[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man Utd: Louis van Gaal gives Luke Shaw Europa League target

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Manchester United manager Louis van Gaal has picked defender Luke Shaw in his Europa League squad to give him a target for his recovery.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Shaw broke his leg against PSV Eindhoven in September, and it is still not known when he will be fit.
The 20-year-old will not be available for the Europa League last-32 encounter with Midtjylland later this month, but Van Gaal has set a longer-term aim.
Van Gaal said: "He can play the final. That is a goal he has to live for."
This year's Europa League final will take place in Basel on 18 May.
