Meanwhile, United midfielder Ander Herrera has dismissed suggestions that former Chelsea boss Jose Mourinho plays a negative brand of football.
Van Gaal has been criticised for his possession-based style of play, and Mourinho has been heavily linked with his job.
The Portuguese has been known for a pragmatic approach, but coached Real Madrid when they won the Spanish league in 2011-12, finishing with 100 points and 121 goals.
Speaking in Spain, Herrera said: "At Chelsea, Mourinho played with Cesc [Fabregas], Willian, Oscar, Hazard and Diego Costa.
"Is this not an attractive style? Or that of his Madrid scoring record in a year?
"Mourinho does not seem to me to be a defensive technician."
